data.title: Ueli “Swiss Machine” Steck (1976
data.meta_description: Ueli Steck, a famous Swiss climber, died Sunday, April 30, 2017, on Mount Everest, according to multiple news sources. He was 40. Steck died while acclimatizing for an attempt on Everest without oxygen by a new route. He was called the Swiss Machine for his methodical approach and his ability to keep going even after...
